//**FORM LOADER USAGE**//

The formLoader.js script dynamically generates forms from JSON configuration files.

Basic Usage:
    <div id="form-container" data-form-loader data-json-path="meds/glp1.json"></div>
    <script src="formLoader.js"></script>

Programmatic Usage:
    // Load a specific form
    await FormLoader.generateForm('meds/glp1.json', 'form-container');
    
    // Load form data only
    const formData = await FormLoader.loadFormData('meds/nad.json');

Available Forms:
    - meds/glp1.json (GLP-1 Weight Loss - 24 questions)
    - meds/nad.json (NAD Anti-Aging - 17 questions)  
    - meds/sermorelin.json (Sermorelin Hormone - 15 questions)

Examples:
    - example-form.html (Basic form selector)
    - advanced-example.html (Advanced demo with metadata)
